The Adverb

65. As adjective. An adverb is occasionally used to modify a noun: eff. 3,.204 f. parvulus iufra cantharus ; 7, 41 leaeo Zonye ferrata domus. This is less natural than in Greek on account of the absence of au article. Examples are rare in the literature of the Republic, but numerous in Livy, Tacitus, and the post—Augustali poets.³
